Necesito aprobación para revisar Gmail/Calendar con `gog`.

Ejecuta exactamente esto:

`/approve allow-once powershell -NoProfile -Command "$env:GOG_ACCOUNT='atlas.ia.agente@gmail.com';
Write-Host '=== FORWARDED / IMPORTANT INBOX ===';
gog gmail messages search 'in:inbox (from:toledo970501@gmail.com OR subject:Fwd OR subject:RV: OR subject:FW: OR subject:Fwd:) newer_than:14d' --max 50 --account atlas.ia.agente@gmail.com;
Write-Host '=== TODAY / DEADLINE KEYWORDS ===';
gog gmail messages search 'in:inbox (today OR hoy OR deadline OR vence OR vencimiento OR due OR due date OR challenge OR interview OR prueba OR test OR task OR pendiente OR reminder OR meeting OR reunión OR factura OR payment OR pago) newer_than:30d' --max 50 --account atlas.ia.agente@gmail.com;
Write-Host '=== UNREAD INBOX ===';
gog gmail messages search 'in:inbox is:unread newer_than:14d' --max 50 --account atlas.ia.agente@gmail.com;
Write-Host '=== CALENDARS ===';
gog calendar list --account atlas.ia.agente@gmail.com"` 

En cuanto lo apruebes, sigo.

arguments.command:
$ErrorActionPreference='Stop'
$headers = @{ 'Authorization' = "Bearer $env:NOTION_TOKEN"; 'Notion-Version' = '2022-06-28'; 'Content-Type' = 'application/json' }
$body = @{ page_size = 100 } | ConvertTo-Json -Depth 10
$r = Invoke-RestMethod -Method Post -Uri 'https://api.notion.com/v1/databases/32f0a0b1-97cc-81a8-9443-df3f85f2ffc7/query' -Headers $headers -Body $body
$r.results | ForEach-Object {
  $p=$_.properties
  [PSCustomObject]@{
    id=$_.id
    name=($p.'Task name'.title.plain_text -join '')
    owner=($p.Owner.rich_text.plain_text -join '')
    status=$p.Status.status.name
    priority=if($p.Priority.select){$p.Priority.select.name}else{''}
    edited=$_.last_edited_time
  }
} | Sort-Object status, owner, name | ConvertTo-Json -Depth 5

